<p>
	Lemon essential oil is well known to be very refreshing to both mind and body, clearing the mind, helping decision making and uplifting the body. It is high in minerals and is often used to strengthen weak nails.</p>
<p>
	Used in an oil burner, a few drops in the bath or blended as a massage oil or cream lemon essential oil is good for colds, the voice, lack of energy, depression and clearing the mind whilst also boosting the immune system and aiding digestion.</p>
<p>
	Lemon has also been known as a painless treatment for warts and verrucas. The therapeutic properties of lemon oil include antimicrobial, anti-rheumatic, anti-sclerotic, antiseptic, bactericidal, carminative, depurative, diaphoretic, diuretic, febrifuge, hypotensive, and insecticidal.</p>
